text.tspan: A survey of 17,096 students in US four-year colleges collected information about
drinking behaviour and alcohol-related problems. Numbers of male and female
'binge-drinkers' (5+ drinks 3 or more times in the past 2 weeks) are shown below.
Are male and female students equally likely to be binge drinkers? If there is a
difference in the probabilities, by how much?
